<tmc-service-paragraph><pub id="RM25T0E"><servcat id="_51"><name>Engine / Hybrid System</name><section id="_029760"><name>1VD-FTV ENGINE CONTROL</name><ttl id="_0282525"><name>ECD SYSTEM(w/ DPF)</name><para id="RM100000000YXUL" category="C"><dtccode>P0122</dtccode><dtcname>Throttle / Pedal Position Sensor / Switch &quot;A&quot; Circuit Low Input</dtcname><dtccode>P0123</dtccode><dtcname>Throttle / Pedal Position Sensor / Switch &quot;A&quot; Circuit High Input</dtcname><dtccode>P0222</dtccode><dtcname>Throttle / Pedal Position Sensor / Switch &quot;B&quot; Circuit Low Input</dtcname><dtccode>P0223</dtccode><dtcname>Throttle / Pedal Position Sensor / Switch &quot;B&quot; Circuit High Input</dtcname><subpara id="RM100000000YXUL_01" category="03"><name>DESCRIPTION</name><content5><ptxt>The throttle position sensor is mounted on the diesel throttle body and detects the opening angle of the throttle valve. This sensor is an electronic sensor and uses Hall-effect elements.</ptxt><ptxt>When the throttle valve is fully closed, a voltage of approximately 0.7 V is applied to terminal VLU of the ECM. The voltage applied to terminal VLU of the ECM increases in proportion to the opening angle of the throttle valve and becomes approximately 3.5 to 4.0 V when the throttle valve is fully opened.</ptxt><ptxt>The ECM determines the vehicle&apos;s driving conditions from the signals input to its terminal VLU. The data is one of the inputs used for EGR control, etc.</ptxt><figure translate="E" type="1"><graphic graphicname="A128639E01" height="3.812598425in" width="7.168479331in"/></figure><table type="dtc-explan-table" pgwide="1"><tgroup cols="6"><colspec colname="1" colwidth="0.71in"/><colspec colname="2" colwidth="1.42in"/><colspec colname="3" colwidth="1.77in"/><colspec colname="4" colwidth="1.77in"/><colspec colname="5" colwidth="0.71in"/><colspec colname="6" colwidth="0.70in"/><thead><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>DTC No.</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Detection Item</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>DTC Detection Condition</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Trouble Area</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>MIL</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Memory</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="dtc-code"><ptxt>P0122</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="detect-item"><ptxt>Throttle / Pedal Position Sensor / Switch &quot;A&quot; Circuit Low Input</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="dtc-detect-cond"><ptxt>Throttle position sensor (for Bank 1) output (VLU) is less than 0.2 V</ptxt><ptxt>(1 trip detection logic)</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="trouble-area"><list1 type="unordered"><item><ptxt>Throttle position sensor (for Bank 1)</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>Open or short in VLU circuit</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>Open in VC circuit</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>ECM</ptxt></item></list1></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="mil"><ptxt>Comes on</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="memory"><ptxt>DTC stored</ptxt></data-name></entry></row><row><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="dtc-code"><ptxt>P0123</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="detect-item"><ptxt>Throttle / Pedal Position Sensor / Switch &quot;A&quot; Circuit High Input</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="dtc-detect-cond"><ptxt>Throttle position sensor (for Bank 1) output (VLU) is more than 4.8 V</ptxt><ptxt>(1 trip detection logic)</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="trouble-area"><list1 type="unordered"><item><ptxt>Throttle position sensor (for Bank 1)</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>Open in E2 circuit</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>VC and VLU circuits are short-circuited</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>ECM</ptxt></item></list1></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="mil"><ptxt>Comes on</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="memory"><ptxt>DTC stored</ptxt></data-name></entry></row><row><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="dtc-code"><ptxt>P0222</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="detect-item"><ptxt>Throttle / Pedal Position Sensor / Switch &quot;B&quot; Circuit Low Input</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="dtc-detect-cond"><ptxt>Throttle position sensor (for Bank 2) output (VLU2) is less than 0.2 V</ptxt><ptxt>(1 trip detection logic)</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="trouble-area"><list1 type="unordered"><item><ptxt>Throttle position sensor (for Bank 2)</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>Open or short in VLU2 circuit</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>Open in VC circuit</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>ECM</ptxt></item></list1></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="mil"><ptxt>Comes on</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="memory"><ptxt>DTC stored</ptxt></data-name></entry></row><row><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="dtc-code"><ptxt>P0223</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="detect-item"><ptxt>Throttle / Pedal Position Sensor / Switch &quot;B&quot; Circuit High Input</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="dtc-detect-cond"><ptxt>Throttle position sensor (for Bank 2) output (VLU2) is more than 4.8 V</ptxt><ptxt>(1 trip detection logic)</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="trouble-area"><list1 type="unordered"><item><ptxt>Throttle position sensor (for Bank 2)</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>Open in E2 circuit</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>VC and VLU2 circuits are short-circuited</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>ECM</ptxt></item></list1></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="mil"><ptxt>Comes on</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="memory"><ptxt>DTC stored</ptxt></data-name></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></content5></subpara><subpara id="RM100000000YXUL_07" category="03"><name>CONFIRMATION DRIVING PATTERN</name><content5><table pgwide="1"><tgroup cols="2"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="2.12in"/><colspec colname="col2" colwidth="4.96in"/><thead><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>DTC No.</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>DTC Detection Drive Pattern</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>P0122</ptxt><ptxt>P0123</ptxt><ptxt>P0222</ptxt><ptxt>P0223</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle"><ptxt>Ignition switch to ON for 3 seconds</ptxt></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></content5></subpara><subpara id="RM100000000YXUL_02" category="03"><name>MONITOR DESCRIPTION</name><content5><ptxt>When the output voltage of the throttle position sensor deviates from the normal operating range (between 0.2 V and 4.8 V) for more than 3 seconds, the ECM interprets this as a malfunction of the sensor circuit and illuminates the MIL.</ptxt><figure type="1" translate="E"><graphic graphicname="C129051E09" width="7.168479331in" height="3.812598425in"/></figure></content5></subpara><subpara id="RM100000000YXUL_03" category="03"><name>WIRING DIAGRAM</name><content5><figure type="1" translate="E"><graphic graphicname="A165736E15" width="7.168479331in" height="5.838041339in"/></figure></content5></subpara><subpara id="RM100000000YXUL_04" category="10"><name>CAUTION / NOTICE / HINT</name><content5><atten3><ptxt>After replacing the ECM, the new ECM needs registration (See page <mlink><xref label="Seep00001" term-id-from="002" href="RM100000000Z1DB"/></mlink>) and initialization (See page <mlink><xref label="Seep00002" term-id-from="002" href="RM100000000YXU9"/></mlink>).</ptxt></atten3><atten4><ptxt>Read freeze frame data using the GTS. Freeze frame data records the engine condition when malfunctions are detected. When troubleshooting, freeze frame data can help determine if the vehicle was moving or stationary, if the engine was warmed up or not, and other data from the time the malfunction occurred.</ptxt></atten4></content5></subpara><subpara id="RM100000000YXUL_06" category="01"><name>PROCEDURE</name><testgrp id="RM100000000YXUL_06_0001" cellposition="1-1"><testtitle>CHECK HARNESS AND CONNECTOR (THROTTLE POSITION SENSOR - ECM)</testtitle><content6><test1><ptxt>Disconnect the throttle position sensor connector.</ptxt><figure type="1" translate="C"><graphic graphicname="A311462C03" width="3.434793307in" height="4.677165354in"/><callout><table pgwide="0" type="caption-table"><tgroup cols="2"><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="0.69in"/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="2.75in"/><tbody><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>*1</ptxt></entry><entry><ptxt>for Bank 1</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>*2</ptxt></entry><entry><ptxt>for Bank 2</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>*a</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle"><ptxt>Front view of wire harness connector</ptxt><ptxt>(to Throttle Position Sensor)</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>*b</ptxt></entry><entry><ptxt>Front view of wire harness connector</ptxt><ptxt>(to ECM)</ptxt></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></callout></figure></test1><test1><ptxt>Disconnect the ECM connector.</ptxt></test1><test1><ptxt>Measure the resistance according to the value(s) in the table below.</ptxt><spec type="other"><title>Standard resistance</title><table><title>for Bank 1</title><tgroup cols="3"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.38in"/><colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.38in"/><colspec colname="col3" colwidth="1.37in"/><thead><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Tester Connection</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Condition</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Specified Condition</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>C50-1 (VC) - C39-110 (VCVL)</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Always</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Below 1 Ω</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>C50-3 (VTA) - C39-64 (VLU)</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Always</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Below 1 Ω</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>C50-2 (E2) - C39-87 (EVLU)</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Always</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Below 1 Ω</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>C50-1 (VC) or C39-110 (VCVL) - Body ground</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Always</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>10 kΩ or higher</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>C50-3 (VTA) or C39-64 (VLU) - Body ground</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Always</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>10 kΩ or higher</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>C50-2 (E2) or C39-87 (EVLU) - Body ground</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Always</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>10 kΩ or higher</ptxt></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><table><title>for Bank 2</title><tgroup cols="3"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.38in"/><colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.38in"/><colspec colname="col3" colwidth="1.37in"/><thead><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Tester Connection</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Condition</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Specified Condition</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>C65-1 (VC) - C39-110 (VCVL)</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Always</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Below 1 Ω</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>C65-3 (VTA) - C39-65 (IG)</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Always</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Below 1 Ω</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>C65-2 (E2) - C39-87 (EVLU)</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Always</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Below 1 Ω</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>C65-1 (VC) or C39-110 (VCVL) - Body ground</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Always</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>10 kΩ or higher</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>C65-3 (VTA) or C39-65 (IG) - Body ground</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Always</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>10 kΩ or higher</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>C65-2 (E2) or C39-87 (EVLU) - Body ground</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Always</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>10 kΩ or higher</ptxt></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></spec></test1><spec type="other"><title>Result</title><table><tgroup cols="1"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="4.13in"/><tbody><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Proceed to</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><judge-value label="1"><ptxt>OK</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><judge-value label="2"><ptxt>NG</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></spec></content6><results><result label="1" cellposition="1-1"><action actiontype="next" cellposition="2-1" childid="RM100000000YXUL_06_0003"/></result><result label="2" cellposition="1-3"><action actiontype="end" cellposition="2-3"><actiontitle>REPAIR OR REPLACE HARNESS OR CONNECTOR</actiontitle><content6/></action></result></results></testgrp><testgrp id="RM100000000YXUL_06_0003" cellposition="2-1"><testtitle>CHECK ECM TERMINAL VOLTAGE (VC TERMINAL)</testtitle><content6><test1><ptxt>Disconnect the throttle position sensor connector.</ptxt><figure type="1" translate="C"><graphic graphicname="A165737C03" width="3.434793307in" height="3.434793307in"/><callout><table pgwide="0" type="caption-table"><tgroup cols="2"><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="0.69in"/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="2.75in"/><tbody><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>*1</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle"><ptxt>for Bank 1</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>*2</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle"><ptxt>for Bank 2</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>*a</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle"><ptxt>Front view of wire harness connector</ptxt><ptxt>(to Throttle Position Sensor)</ptxt></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></callout></figure></test1><test1><ptxt>Measure the voltage according to the value(s) in the table below.</ptxt><spec type="other"><title>Standard voltage</title><table><title>for Bank 1</title><tgroup cols="3"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.38in"/><colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.38in"/><colspec colname="col3" colwidth="1.37in"/><thead><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Tester Connection</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Switch Condition</ptxt></e